00:03:55.570 --> 00:03:58.450
hoping to find gold and treasure.

00:03:58.450 --> 00:04:02.170
I wonder if there are still any
tombs or treasures left to be found.

00:04:02.170 --> 00:04:03.600
There may be.

00:04:04.510 --> 00:04:07.310
By the way, where did the old man go?

00:04:07.600 --> 00:04:08.990
To the bathroom.

00:04:08.990 --> 00:04:11.820
Iggy's with him, so if anything
seems odd, they'll notice.

00:04:11.820 --> 00:04:13.250
Bathroom?

00:04:13.250 --> 00:04:14.450
Do you need to go, too?

00:04:16.090 --> 00:04:18.480
If it's a <i>real</i> bathroom, sure.

00:04:25.270 --> 00:04:28.000
Oh my God!

00:04:31.660 --> 00:04:36.850
The air's so dry, the poop turns
into dust and flies away.

00:04:37.300 --> 00:04:40.760
So instead of using water,
this toilet uses the wind?

00:04:41.050 --> 00:04:43.290
And there's no paper.

00:04:44.520 --> 00:04:45.770
This is...

00:04:49.610 --> 00:04:53.150
Could this be a sand washlet?!

00:04:53.150 --> 00:04:56.090
You clean your ass... with sand?!

00:04:56.750 --> 00:04:58.870
Desert sand is sterile.

00:04:58.870 --> 00:05:01.950
Oh my God!

00:05:04.700 --> 00:05:08.130
I'm not Polnareff, but I think I'll
wait until we're at the hotel.

00:05:08.630 --> 00:05:14.060
