I might as well just go behind a rock.

00:05:14.060 --> 00:05:16.660
That's a strange sight to see in Egypt.

00:05:29.290 --> 00:05:32.040
This makes no sense.

00:05:32.040 --> 00:05:35.980
Why is there an electrical outlet in this rock?

00:05:36.430 --> 00:05:38.450
What would you even use it for?

00:05:38.450 --> 00:05:41.240
It's not like it could be wired to anything.

00:05:46.060 --> 00:05:48.430
I-It shocked me...

00:05:48.430 --> 00:05:50.770
Mr. Joestar, what's the matter?

00:05:50.770 --> 00:05:52.430
We're going to head out soon.

00:05:53.030 --> 00:05:55.380
Huh? R-Right...

00:05:55.750 --> 00:05:57.790
Got it. I'll be right there.

00:05:58.710 --> 00:06:01.900
But what a surprise that was...

00:06:01.900 --> 00:06:04.080
Since there's power running to it,

00:06:04.080 --> 00:06:06.770
does that mean they
have electricity around here?

00:06:07.580 --> 00:06:10.440
What a strange place.

00:06:10.440 --> 00:06:12.610
How surreal...

00:06:21.760 --> 00:06:24.690
Bam

00:06:26.780 --> 00:06:30.930
Her card represents the Goddess Bastet.
The user's name is Mariah.

00:06:36.360 --> 00:06:41.230
You always want to touch what's off-limits.

00:06:54.730 --> 00:06:59.780
We could make it to Cairo in two
days, but we're all injured.

00:06:59.780 --> 00:07:04.270
Why don't we spend tonight and
tomorrow in Luxor to take a break?

00:07:06.400 --> 00:07:09.690
Let's do that. Ever since we got to Egypt,

00:07:09.690 --> 00:07:12.470
the enemy Stands have been getting stronger.

00:07:12.900 --> 00:07:15.510
We've just barely been winning.

00:07:17.080 --> 00:07:19.550
Hey, Mr. Joestar, is something wrong?

00:07:20.420 --> 00:07:23.380
My prosthetic hand's been acting up.

00:07:23.380 --> 00:07:26.680
Well, I'm sure the joints just need oiling.

00:07:26.680 --> 00:07:30.810
Hey! Isn't that radio broken?

00:07:30.810 --> 00:07:35.730
How strange. It's made in Japan,
and I just bought it...

00:07:36.030 --> 00:07:38.900
That static's irritating! Could you turn it off?

00:07:40.700 --> 00:07:42.010
Mr. Joestar?

00:07:42.690 --> 00:07:49.000
Yeah, I agree. We should probably
rest up before we enter Cairo.

00:07:49.780 --> 00:07:52.060
But we cannot let our guard down.

00:07:53.410 --> 00:07:55.040
All right. Let's find a hotel.

00:07:56.180 --> 00:07:58.050
How strange.

00:07:58.050 --> 00:07:59.490
Thanks, old man.

00:07:59.490 --> 00:08:00.800
Ah, thank you!

00:08:24.610 --> 00:08:27.450
